{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, the binary interaction in (3), on average, brings the agent opinion closer to the one of leaders since they are not affected by the population opinion.In the kinetic approach, the statistical description of the agents of the population is obtained through the distribution function f = f (t, A, w), t ≥ 0.",
    "This means that f (t, A, w)dAdw represents the number of agents with opinion in [w, w + dw] and level of activity in [A, A + dA] at time t ≥ 0.",
    "Without loss of generality, we may assume that ∫ R×I f (0, A, w)dAdw = 1.",
    "We will be interested in studying the evolution of the mass fractions of each part of the population, i.e.",
    "active, undecided, and inactive, respectively given byρ a (t) = ∫ I×(γ,+∞) f (t, A, w)dAdw,(6)ρ u (t) = ∫ I×(-γ,γ) f (t, A, w)dAdw,(7)ρ i (t) = ∫ I×(-∞,-γ) f (t, A, w)dAdw,(8)and clearly ∑ j∈{a,u,i} ρ j (0) = 1."
  ]
}